HEADWORD: Miff
<hw>Miff</hw> <pr>(m⟦icr⟧f)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Prov. G.
<ets>muff</ets> sullenness, sulkiness, <ets>muffen</ets> to be silky,
<ets>muff⟦ium⟧g</ets> sullen, pouting.]</ety> <def>A petty falling out;
a tiff; a quarrel; offense.</def> <rj><au>Fielding.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miff</ent>⟦br⟧

